-- Security properties
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- (no security requirements provided)


----------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Fixed type error: Schedule_Database was incorrectly used as both Interface and Resource; introduced ScheduleData as the concrete Resource and adjusted all references.
-- Summary 2: Fixed contradictory test case predicates that assumed op.post = op.pre for rejection (violated inv_state_must_change); changed to op.post = Post2 (rejection state).
-- Summary 3: Fixed incorrect use of channel.kind in ac_reach_3; replaced with channel membership.
-- Summary 4: Added role_permissions fact to assign meaningful permissions to actors (previously unconstrained).
-- Summary 5: Adjusted test case assertions to be mutually consistent with post-states and invariants.
-- Assumption 1: Actors have fixed permission sets: Scheduler has all permissions, Resource_Manager has Read+Write, Project_Team has Read.
-- Assumption 2: The system always transitions to a different state (pre != post) even on rejection; Post2 represents the error-displaying state.
-- Assumption 3: The schedule database is modeled as a Resource (ScheduleData) owned by some actor; its accessibility is left unconstrained to allow exploration.
-- Assumption 4: Overlap detection is implied by the state outcome (Post1/Post2) but not explicitly modeled as a temporal property.
-- Open issue 1: The model lacks explicit representation of slots, time, and overlap predicates; it only captures abstract authorization and state transitions. Overlap detection logic is not formalized.
-- Open issue 2: The same state Post2 is used for both 'error displayed' and 'rejection' without distinguishing different error messages.
-- Open issue 3: Edge case assertions (ec_safe_1..3) are not directly tied to the requirement and may be disconnected from the functional goal.


